&gt; Betreff: [junit] Suggestion: New addition to the Assert class
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Most of my tests have a catch all, catch block, which simplay calls
&gt; fail(e.toString());
&gt;
&gt; Can i suggest that the following fail() method be added for the next
&gt; release.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; 	/**
&gt; 	 * Fails a test with the given message.
&gt; 	 */
&gt; 	static public void fail(Exception e) {
&gt; 		throw new AssertionFailedError(e.toString());
&gt; 	}
&gt;
&gt; Seems to make the code cleaner, my 2cents
&gt;
